<item>
            <title>[WICKET-6528] Component part of Page check in AjaxRequestHandler breaks applications</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-6528</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The check if a component is part of the page hierarchy where an Ajax response is generated for breaks client applications in a most unpleasant way. While this check is good&#8482;, it should only generate errors&#160;in development mode. In deployment mode it should ignore the component (like in versions prior to Wicket 8) and log it as an error (which is expected: the application is in error).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See method `public void add(Component... components)` in AjaxRequestHandler for more details.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13136264">WICKET-6528</key>
