                            <comment id="16352339" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 5 Feb 2018 12:58:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 60c94cd6927a2ec6962639ead96f57f127f954e5 in wicket&apos;s branch refs/heads/&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-6528&quot; title=&quot;Component part of Page check in AjaxRequestHandler breaks applications&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-6528&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-6528&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dashorst&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dashorst&quot;&gt;dashorst&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=wicket.git;h=60c94cd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=wicket.git;h=60c94cd&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t block user when component not on Page using AJAX&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Re-instate the behavior that was in versions &amp;lt; 8.0 that a component&lt;br/&gt;
added to an AjaxRequestTarget but is not part of the page, would be&lt;br/&gt;
ignored (or failed to refresh with an error in the JavaScript console).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So instead of always throwing an error, we only do so in DEVELOPMENT&lt;br/&gt;
mode causing an error page, and in DEPLOYMENT mode we only log the&lt;br/&gt;
fault, but don&apos;t break the application hard for the user: the component&lt;br/&gt;
refresh is ignored, just as it would&apos;ve been in versions prior to 8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixes &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-6528&quot; title=&quot;Component part of Page check in AjaxRequestHandler breaks applications&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-6528&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-6528&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
